   "source": [
    "# IFRS 9 Stage 2 Migration Prediction — ML Pipeline\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Objective**: Predict which performing (Stage 1) loans will migrate to IFRS 9 Stage 2  \n",
    "> (Significant Increase in Credit Risk — SICR) within the next 90 days.  \n",
    "> **Dataset**: 84,098 UK bank loans across 7 product types, 16 quarterly snapshots (2021-Q1 → 2024-Q4)  \n",
    "> **Target**: `stage_2_migration` (Binary: 0 = remains Stage 1, 1 = migrates to Stage 2)  \n",
    "> **Class ratio**: ~22% positive (imbalanced — optimise for Recall + PR-AUC)\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "### Notebook Structure\n",
    "| Section | Description |\n",
    "|---------|-------------|\n",
    "| **1. Setup & Data Loading** | Install libs, load data, first look |\n",
    "| **2. EDA** | Distributions, correlations, temporal analysis, target analysis |\n",
    "| **3. Feature Engineering** | 50+ risk features, sentinel handling, encoding |\n",
    "| **4. Time-Based Train/Val/Test Split** | Chronological split, no data leakage |\n",
    "| **5. Model Training** | XGBoost, LightGBM, CatBoost with Optuna tuning |\n",
    "| **6. Evaluation** | ROC-AUC, PR-AUC, Recall@Top10%, business metrics |\n",
    "| **7. Explainability** | SHAP global + local, top risk drivers |\n",
    "| **8. Export Artifacts** | Pickle models, preprocessor, feature list, configs |\n"
   ]
  },
